headline: Mastercard Faces Fee Pressure As Truist Open Banking Deal Builds Services
summary: Large merchants, including Walmart, are seeking oral arguments in a long running settlement dispute over card interchange fees with Mastercard and Visa. The case focuses on how much merchants pay to accept Mastercard and Visa cards, with potential implications for future fee structures. Separately, Mastercard has partnered with Truist Financial to use Mastercard open finance technology for secure, user controlled open banking connectivity.
